                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-05T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 5, 1931—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9: 05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. In conformity with section 17 of article 72 of the Constitution Congress
                    today at noon declared a state of siege throughout the Republic for a period of
                    one month. The proclamation of the law will probably be made tonight. This
                    action by Congress is tantamount to the creation of a constitutional civil
                    dictatorship. However, actually the Army is the effective force in control.</p>
                <p>Except for the presence of soldiers in the city the situation in Santiago is
                    normal. Streetcar service resumed this afternoon but definite settlement not
                    reached.</p>
                <p>Unless Government ultimatum for unconditional surrender of the fleet at Coquimbo
                    is complied with, attack on ships will be made tonight or tomorrow morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
